Taeniogonalos
Schulz, 1906: 212; 
Weinstein and Austin 1991
: 416; 
Tsuneki 1991
: 59; 
Carmean and Kimsey 1998
: 65. Type species (by monotypy): 
Trigonalys maculata
Smith, 1851.

Poecilogonalos
Schulz, 1906: 212; 
Marshakov 1981
: 105; 
Tsuneki 1991
: 46; 
Weinstein and Austin 1991
: 422; 
Tsuneki 1991
: 46; 
Lelej 1995
: 14. Type species (by monotypy): 
Trigonalys thwaitesii
Westwood, 1874. Synonymized by 
Carmean and Kimsey 1998
.

Reared as hyperparasitoid of parasitoid wasps (
Ichneumonidae
and 
Braconidae
) and parasitoid flies (
Tachinidae
) in caterpillars, but some species are primary parasitoids of Pergid sawflies in Australia (
Raff 1934
; 
Carne 1969
; 
He and Chen 1986
; 
Weinstein and Austin 1995
; 
Carmean and Kimsey 1998
).
